						               													<description>From the box: &amp;quot;Draw a Category Card and roll the Letter Die to select a letter. Everyone has ONE MINUTE to write things from the selected category that start with the letter on the die. THINK FAST! WRITE FAST!&amp;quot;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This Scattegories-type game includes a die with every letter of the alphabet on it, plus some sides that say &amp;quot;Vowel&amp;quot;, meaning the rolling player chooses a vowel.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;According to the rules, a game consists of each player taking a turn flipping up a card with a category written on it (such as &amp;quot;sports teams&amp;quot;) and rolling the letter die, and then all players have one minute (timer not included) to write down (paper and pencils not included) as many words starting with that letter as possible.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player gains one point per word, and any unique words (ones that other players don't have), then it is worth two points.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game finishes when each player has rolled the die three times. The highest score wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
